Johannesburg Mayor Mpho Phalatse has promised shelter to the victims of a fire that saw hundreds of homes destroyed in the city centre. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Johannesburg Mayor Mpho Phalatse has promised shelter to the victims of a fire that saw hundreds of homes destroyed in the city centre. The blaze that broke out on Sunday morning in the Kwa Mai Mai informal settlement. READ: UPDATE | Fire breaks out near Kwa Mai Mai in JHB Over 400 families are without homes. Meanwhile, illegal connections are thought to be the cause of the fire. Watch the video above for more details.